  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "GitHub is widely used across various industries and by a multitude of companies and startups, ranging from small tech startups to large enterprises. Some notable companies and organizations that utilize GitHub include:\n\n1. **Microsoft** - After acquiring GitHub in 2018, Microsoft has integrated GitHub deeply into its development processes and offers various tools and services that complement GitHub, like Azure DevOps.\n\n2. **Google** - Google uses GitHub for several open-source projects and encourages developers to share their work on the platform.\n\n3. **Facebook** - Facebook has open-sourced many of its projects on GitHub, such as React, GraphQL, and more.\n\n4. **Netflix** - Netflix uses GitHub for its numerous open-source projects and libraries, which are available for public use.\n\n5. **Twitter** - Twitter has various open-source tools and libraries hosted on GitHub, contributing to the developer community.\n\n6. **Spotify** - Spotify shares several of its open-source projects on GitHub, allowing developers to contribute and use its tools.\n\n7. **Airbnb** - Airbnb has open-sourced several tools and libraries on GitHub, fostering a community around its technology.\n\n8. **Uber** - Uber has a presence on GitHub, where it shares various open-source projects and libraries related to its services.\n\nIn addition to these larger companies, countless startups leverage GitHub for version control, collaboration, and open-source contributions. Some notable startups include:\n\n1. **Docker** - Known for containerization technology, Docker maintains its projects on GitHub.\n\n2. **Slack** - Slack has open-sourced parts of its technology stack and engages with the developer community on GitHub.\n\n3. **Stripe** - The payment processing platform uses GitHub to host its open-source libraries and tools.\n\n4. **Figma** - The collaborative design tool uses GitHub for version control in its development processes.\n\n5. **Notion** - Notion has shared some of its tools and libraries on GitHub, contributing to the open-source community.\n\nThese examples highlight GitHub's role as a critical platform for software development, collaboration, and open-source initiatives across various sectors.",
